name: Ecs
comment:
# Specs

Specs specify how to retrieve and update components and singletons.
They are initialized using the **Ecs.ComponentsN** and **Ecs.SingletonsN** modules.

    type alias Specs =
        { allComponents : AllComponentsSpec EntityId Components
        , position : ComponentSpec EntityId Position Components
        , velocity : ComponentSpec EntityId Velocity Components
        , nextEntityId : SingletonSpec EntityId Singletons
        }

    specs : Specs
    specs =
        Specs |> Ecs.Components2.specs |> Ecs.Singletons1.specs

@docs AllComponentsSpec, ComponentSpec, SingletonSpec


# World

The world contains all your entities, components and singletons.

@docs World, emptyWorld, isEmptyWorld, worldEntities
@docs worldEntityCount, worldComponentCount


# Entity

Entities are represented by an id.
An entity id can be any [`comparable` type](https://faq.elm-community.org/#does-elm-have-ad-hoc-polymorphism-or-typeclasses).

Operations on entities usually apply to the active entity in the world.
You can make an entity active with the [**onEntiy**](#onEntity) function.
Also when you insert a new entity that entity will be active.

@docs insertEntity, onEntity, removeEntity, clearEntity, hasEntity, getEntity


# Component

Components contain all the entity data in the world.
Every component is associated with an entity.

@docs insertComponent, updateComponent, removeComponent
@docs hasComponent, getComponent, componentEntities, componentCount
@docs setComponents, clearComponents, getComponents


# Singletons

Singletons contain data where there should only be one instance of.
Singletons are optional. They are added to the package for convenience
and to create a consistent way to deal with data (singletons and components).
You can also just keep the singleton data in your model next to the ecs world just like you do in any Elm program.

@docs setSingleton, updateSingleton, getSingleton

aliases.name: AllComponentsSpec
aliases.comment: Used for operations on multiple component types.

aliases.name: ComponentSpec
aliases.comment: Used for operations on a single component type.

aliases.name: SingletonSpec
aliases.comment: Used for operations on a single singleton type.

aliases.name: World
aliases.comment: The world that contains all you data.

values.name: clearComponents
values.comment: Clear all components for the specified component type.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: clearEntity
values.comment:
Remove all components of the active entity.
The entity will remain part of the world.
values.type: Ecs.AllComponentsSpec comparable components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: componentCount
values.comment: Determine the total number of components of the specified component type.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Basics.Int

values.name: componentEntities
values.comment: Get all entities that contain the specified component type.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Set.Set comparable

values.name: emptyWorld
values.comment:
Create an empty world without entities or components.
Singletons need an intial value.
values.type: Ecs.AllComponentsSpec comparable components -> singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: getComponent
values.comment: Get a component with the specified component type of the active entity.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Maybe.Maybe a

values.name: getComponents
values.comment: Get all components for the specified component type.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Dict.Dict comparable a

values.name: getEntity
values.comment: Get the active entity id.
values.type: Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Maybe.Maybe comparable

values.name: getSingleton
values.comment: Get the data for the specified singleton type.
values.type: Ecs.SingletonSpec a singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> a

values.name: hasComponent
values.comment: Determine if the active entity has the specified component type.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Basics.Bool

values.name: hasEntity
values.comment: Determine if there is an active entity.
values.type: Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Basics.Bool

values.name: insertComponent
values.comment: Insert a component with the specified component type in the active entity.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> a -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: insertEntity
values.comment: Add a new entity id to the world and make the entity active.
values.type: comparable -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: isEmptyWorld
values.comment: Determine if the world is empty, without entities or components.
values.type: Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Basics.Bool

values.name: onEntity
values.comment: Make an entity active if it is part of the world, otherwise no entity will be active.
values.type: comparable -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: removeComponent
values.comment: Remove a component with the specified component type from the active entity.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: removeEntity
values.comment:
Remove the active entity from the world.
All component associated with the entity will also be removed.
values.type: Ecs.AllComponentsSpec comparable components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: setComponents
values.comment:
Replace all components for the specified component type.
All provided entities are added to the world.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> Dict.Dict comparable a -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: setSingleton
values.comment: Set the data for the specified singleton type.
values.type: Ecs.SingletonSpec a singletons -> a -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: updateComponent
values.comment: Update a component with the specified component type in the active entity.
values.type: Ecs.ComponentSpec comparable a components -> (Maybe.Maybe a -> Maybe.Maybe a) -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: updateSingleton
values.comment: Update the data for the specified singleton type.
values.type: Ecs.SingletonSpec a singletons -> (a -> a) -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons

values.name: worldComponentCount
values.comment: Determine the total number of components in the world.
values.type: Ecs.AllComponentsSpec comparable components -> Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Basics.Int

values.name: worldEntities
values.comment: Get all entity ids in the world.
values.type: Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Set.Set comparable

values.name: worldEntityCount
values.comment: Determine the total number of entities in the world.
values.type: Ecs.World comparable components singletons -> Basics.Int

values.name: specs
values.comment: Create all component specifications for 1 component type.
values.type: (Ecs.Internal.AllComponentsSpec comparable (Ecs.Components1.Components1 comparable a1) -> Ecs.Internal.ComponentSpec comparable a1 (Ecs.Components1.Components1 comparable a1) -> specs) -> specs
